Something is wrong... I can feel it in my bones. Don't know with what or with who, I just don't know. Why can't I just figure out what it is already, because its tearing me apart.

"Sometimes I lie awake at night and ask myself 'why me?' Then a voice answers, 'Nothing personal, your name just came up." -Charlie Brown 

     So I don't really know what to write about or where to start or anything. I don't think anything will help me figure out what's going on in my life right now. I'm tired of being lied to and used and lonely. I could talk about it until I'm blue in the face and I still wouldn't say everything I want to say. Josh says that he gives up on me because I try to be tough and don't open up. Maybe he's right. For those few of you that actually bother to care... I'm not worth the effort. I don't give a fuck anymore... about school, about my family, about my friends, about just fucking life. The only reason I'm going to school right now is to take up my time... while I'm getting some money together... and then I'm out of here, and I'll be damned if I ever come back to Parma again. So don't bother worrying about me, don't waste the effort. I'll just end up being a dissapointment to everyone, and Lord knows I know what its like to be disappointed. Not a good feeling. Especially when that's all that you have in your life. In a few years, I'll be long gone and long forgotten, and it'll be for the best. Everyone will be better off, and maybe I will too. It's just not worth it, the way everything is now... This can't be all that's out there.

So.... I'm bored.. .and I was in a creative mood, but not so creative... so I thought I'd share some poems that I wrote a long time ago... one about WWI... for a class.. and the other one just for no reason.  The one is going into a BW book thingie of different stories and poems and stuff, so I thought I'd share with my friends before sharing with the whole world.  They're pretty crappy, but its fun anyways.  

Lost

I knew a young boy
Who grinned at life in simple ecstasy
A boy of nineteen who flirted with beauties in the park
Making mischief of a young boy
All too soon the hands of his brokenhearted girl are empty

War is the total pain of millions of parted loved ones - some for always

The dawn breaking, the sky filling with light
The trumpets filling the air
The new young soldier lays on the freshly dewed grass
Staring across the morning, heavy with fog
Not knowing what tomorrow brings

War is the impossibility of planning a future
Uncertainty that mocks every hoping dream

The soldier boy prays
As his weary hands carry wounded comrades
Over bloody battlefields
The ghostly cries of wounded echo through the front

War is the many precious years of human life lost

The soldier boy watches as his companion fights for his life
Bitterness sweeping through him
He was young, he hated the war
How should he die as he wrong prevails

Death chose him, and he went
The cruel evening became silent
Then - far away, the gentle boom of a rifle

War is the corpse of a friend;
One moment ago a living human being
With thoughts, hopes, and a future
Now only a memory

The soldier boy hangs his head
Not to daunt the coming twilight
He whispers:
"You did not die in vain."

That was the WWI one.. I must add... I know that a lot of you are not going to like my poems... they're not anti-war... I don't mean them to be, its just looking at it from people's perspectives not from the basic idea of it.  I do think that there is a just cause for certain wars, but there are people and families to think about.   ANYways.... this is my other one... I like this one better

Fallen Angels

They crave to be safe at home surrounded by love
They pray to God that they don't die
Each day that passes, they long to be safe in their haven 
They have not experienced life yet, 
Now they will pay the greatest debt

Shattered Dreams
No longer have wings 

The night sky is on fire
The lives of boys who dreamed of glory
Forever tainted
Not knowing what becomes of tomorrow
Fighting the exhaustion that threatens to overcome
Vivid memories flash before their eyes

Shattered Dreams
No longer have wings

They were told to fight, and they shall be free
As rain streams from the sky
Sanity slipping fast
Another shot is fired
They long to be safe in the arms of loved ones
Enveloped in the smells of sweet perfume and freshly baked pie
They wonder how a freedom
Can make the bravest of men run in fear
In wars such as this who is to say who won or lost
Men will die, widows will cry
When will this end?

Shattered Dreams
No longer have wings

As my companions fall
A tear slides down my cheek
For Shattered  Dreams
No longer have wings
Souls abandoned
A soldier's glory missed

What Age Do You Act?

umm.... so yeah. Fuck school. I'm just going to stop going now. It's not worth my parents spending all the money when its just not happening. I actually love my history class... as I do all my history classes, but what would I do with that. It sucks... why do some people know exactly what they want to be. They go into college, knowing without a doubt exactly what they like, what they want to do with the rest of they're lives. There's so much out there, how can I just pick one thing and do it for the rest of my life. There is nothing out there that interests me like that... except singing, but well -- I'm not good enough... well, that about ends that debate. I hate that my parents keep pushing me towards making that decision. Who's life is it... mine or theirs?? Its not my fault that they never finished school or did what they wanted to do with their lives. Another thing that sucks.... anything that I actually do want to do.... music or history, there's no future in that. Why can't I just be good at science and math where all the good jobs are. No, I have to be fucked up and like things that aren't real jobs unless you get a PhD. Another fucked up thing... PhDs. Why the fuck would I want to stay in school for half of my life. What is that going to do for me. Do you really learn that much more going to school for eight more years than everyone else just for the fucking title of doctor. By then you're old and gray and since you've been going to school all your life you didn't have time to marry, so you're old gray and lonely. Great life I got ahead of me. My dad used to play me in the game Old Maid, and usually he would let me win, but when I started getting older he got harder on me so I would lose and he'd laugh and say I was the Old Maid. What if that's just my destiny. I'm done. I can't make this decision. How can I possibly plan the rest of my life at the age of 18. It's just not possible. What if I get a degree, and then there's no jobs in the field. Then I'm screwed. Its stupid. Why can't we all just go back to farming or something. 
Some times I feel that people are just waiting for me to fuck up. Like... they see me and they're just thinking... "wow... she sucks at life, that girl's not going anywhere". Sometimes, you just see it in people's eyes even though they won't say it. It doesn't matter to me, I guess, I just think people should look at themselves before judging me. 
I mean... my life isn't SO terrible... I have some good friends, and they get me through a lot, but they're always screwed too... I just wonder... is it always going to be me and my friends that get the shaft. Why us.... why not the assholes. Why is it that the nice, funny, down to earth people get fucked. Why are we the ones with fucked up family lives and the no luck love lives. It doesn't seem fair. I know... life's not fair, but why not. It sucks. Friends. They're a funny thing. I love them much, but it really sucks when they disappoint you. Especially the ones you never expected. Lately, I don't know, I just feel like I'm in the way. More than usual. Like I'm an expendable resource. "Well, I guess talk to/hang out with Diana for a bit, until someone better come along..." Which, I guess I can't blame them. I don't really have much to say anymore. It's like... I'm not part of anything anymore. 
The fact that Valentine's Day is on the way... not making me too happy either. It's just another day, but... its still there, out to depress people like me who don't have anyone. At least I'm not in high school with all the damn pink, and flowers and chocolate for everyone but me... no.... that sucks, I don't mean to bitch about that, I'm happy for those people that they found someone that they like... its just a little "rub it in my face" kinda thing sometimes. Things just haven't been right for a long time.  I keep saying that I'm going to start over... I think its time to do that. Yes... that's what I'm going to do. New beginnings. New everything, with everyone. We'll see what comes of that. 

An appropriate song... I'm not too big a fan of "new" Green Day, but I like this song a lot, mostly for its sentimental value, and like the song says... sometimes I wish someone out there will find me, until then I walk alone. I'm ok with that. Content is a good word for it. I'm content.

So.... break has been over for a week, but it just seems like its ending now for me because everyone left me. So I'm going to overview my break. My break was.... actually pretty good. I spent the first part of it working... .a LOT... and Rudy's sucks, but its cool. Rudy's is hilareous though, its always interesting to be there. Everything's shifting there... and Danielle is cleaning out Euge's stuff.... and oh boy some of the stuff she found. Lol... apparently she found a dead mouse in the back of the room and Janet freaked out.... but nobody is as scared of mice as Julie. She won't even go downstairs into the basement because she thinks there are mice there. So Danielle and Janet... being two of the adults of the place.... took the dead mouse and put it in a box. Then Danielle was like... Julie can you help me with some of these boxes, and has Julie get the one with the mouse. Julie picks it up, looks inside, all that's in there is the mouse and she throws the box in the air and screams MOTHERFUCKER!!! Then she proceeds to swear up a storm... you stupid bitch I hate you, fuck.... as customers are walking in. Danielle was laughing so hard she couldn't even finish the story. So add that to my adventures at Rudy's. Oh yeah.... DEANNA was FIRED!!! What a sweet sweet world this is. Rudy's is extra pissing me off right now, cause they hired a new girl already and I have to work with her the next two weeks cause Christy is off.. which would be fine, if it wasn't Friday and Saturday.. which I have piano and CYM on those days. It sucks. 
My favorite part of break??? The fact that I didn't have to hang out with anyone I didn't like. Well except New Years, but I quickly got over that when everyone was making fun of her. That was great. I spent a lot of time with Tamara... especially when Nina was here... and that was fun, Nina is a cool girl and I'm glad I met her. I miss her... east coast is so damn far away... especially since you've lived walking distance from me all my life. We always know how to have fun, even if it means skipping out on church and playing poker on Christmas eve. There were a few Denny's trips with Abby, Danielle, Jen O'Malley.... gotta love the Denny's trips. 
I loved that I got to spend time with Bails because I don't see her that often while she's at school... though I'm going to try to come up to Kent more often this semester because I miss spending time with her, Circus Atari.... nothing will ever beat it, that guy being smooshed and kicking his feet in the air, that was the most hilareous thing, except maybe the dog that chased your car later that night. It was great hanging out with Josh, Shane, and Bails.... because, as Bails said, they are the people I feel most comfortable around. I can tell them anything... and we always have an awesome time even if its just sitting at Denny's for hours upon end. Especially when we're picking on Josh. I know them probably better than I know myself and vice-versa. I love you guys, just wanted you to know that, thanks for staying close. So yeah, pretty much my break was uneventful, but I like it the way it was. 
So my new semester has started... I'm taking a History of Russia class and its pretty cool, a lot like Ukie school right now, which is great. I have an 8 in the morning math class... who does that.... and I just don't know what's going on. Well.. I guess I would if I was awake... but whatever. I'm taking a personal wellness class, whatever the fuck that is.... its basically health class that's mandatory... and just for the "minimester" or 7 weeks. Since I was thinking about majoring in buisness I figured I should take a buisness class.... so I took management... its ok... all next week we're watching Office Space, which is a hilareous movie. I have an evening class.... Industrial/Organizational Psychology.... I've only been to one so far, but its pretty much buisness... just with a psych title... it was my advisors last attempt to keep me as a psych major (which doesn't look like its going to happen). Ha... that's my usual wednesday right there. I dont' have the I/O pysch class on Mon or Fri. My last class is my only Tuesday/Thursday one.... its.... dun dun dun... physics. My professor is crazy. He looks like a hippie... with this long ass beard and long hair that he pulls into a ponytail and these really thick glasses. The way he talks too... He makes me laugh. That class I think is going to be a little challenging... especially to stay awake in. I dont know if I'm going to be able to handle relativity and quantum theory and all that jazz. The fact that he spells the word phenomenon on the board phenomenom... I don't know... but yeah. Schedule isn't that bad. It's just that this week went by like a freaking month. I always hate spring semester... it goes by so slow. I can't wait till summertime. Well... anyways... I think this is enough ramblings for one day, just trying to catch up because I haven't written in a while. Peace out....

It was actually a normal story... about a twelve year old kid and his three friends who go on a journey to find a dead body of a boy and how they bonded and stuff.  Its a really cute movie... even with its cheezy 80s motif, and like so many other 80s movies its based in the 50s so it has some jammin tunes, ha ha.  As a plus it has Corey Feldman before he became a dork as a crazy kid and Kiefer Sutherland pre-24 days.  My favorite by far... River Phoenix.... not only was he little Indiana Jones, a Marine in Dogfight, have an awesome name, and lived a rock star life (OD'd at the age of 23), but he was pretty cute... and in the movie he's a tough guy, but you definitely get the soft side.      Then I went to "You suck cause you're an American" class where I learned more about how Americans are stupid, uncultured people, how Malasians have to know many languages, and how Malasians are cultured because they hear Muslims sing prayers every morning even if they're not Muslim, and how Americans are racist. Then people wonder why I hate learning about Asian cultures. I don't like learning about Asian cultures.  I hate that she says that she's Malasian-Chinese like I'm supposed to bow down to her.  Just because she knows five languages and I know two doesn't make her more cultured than me.  I think America is more cultured.... in Malasia, they do what the Malasians do, in China they do what the Chinese do... in America they do all of that.  Every family can celebrate what holidays they want, and follow what traditions they want.  Sure there are people who don't follow any traditions, but that's what they want... and they can do what they want unlike in Communist China where they'll be quietly extinguished because they don't agree with the government and Chinese traditions.  I'm not in that class to learn about how much my country sucks because we're uncultured, I'm there to learn about music.  I don't understand her either, and she gets pissed cause we don't, but that's another story.  You know what I say to that... she can take your Chinese-Malasian, five language speaking culture... and shove it.  Sorry to anyone I've offended, I'm just tired of her racist badmouthing of white people.

So if my life wasn't confusing enough, I went to go see the Falsetto Trilogy at BW tonight with Crysten.  Man, was it fucked up.  The first act was just rediculous. What do Thomas Jefferson, Pope Leo XIII, Jules Verne, Edgar Allen Poe, and Ben Franklin have in common?  No it's not a joke, sorry... there's no clever punchline.  I'm not good with jokes anyway.  But I did figure out the secret.  In World Civ class the other day, we were talking about Descartes. Very interesting dude he was.  Particularly his theory of deductive reasoning.  He started to accept only priori truths and conclusions that flowed logically from those truths.  A Priori is a truth found in a manner which is independent of experience.  Decartes went as far as saying that we cannot accept anything that comes from sensory perception.  So this computer may not really be there, or the people I'm talking to aren't real, or the next step you take the floor might not be there kind of thing. For example: Something cannot exist or not exist at the same time.  This is true.  It just can't.  A very famous a priori truth stated by Descartes is "I think, therefore I am."  This is how he proved that he himself existed.  Nobody else was proven existent, so its possible that we are all figments of Descartes' mind.  I do have a point in all this... besides trying to convince everyone that I'm on ganja.  My professor tells us that Descartes had a major opium habit.  This got me thinking.  The answer to my first question: they were all drug users.  So I looked it up online... here's what I came up with:
*marijuana: Thomas Jefferson,Bob Marley, Jim Morrison, The Beatles,George Washington, Al Gore, Newt Gingrich, Bill Clinton
*cocaine:Thomas Edison, Jules Verne, Pope Leo XIII, Sigmund Freud (who would have guessed)
*mushrooms: Jesus, Lewis Carrol
*heroin/opium: Janis Joplin,Picasso, Edgar Allen Poe, Ben Franklin, Descartes
Which also gets me to crazy people... John Forbes Nash,Jr., Albert Einstein,Vincent Van Gogh... all schitzophrenics.  So for all those people like me who want to be famous some day and don't know where they're headed in life... be crazy... all the geniuses were... and if you're not a genius, just take a hit of that blunt... because it seems that's the way to do it.  I should write a book... how to become famous.  It'll be a best seller, brought to you by crack cocaine.  That's all I have to say for right now... I was just in one of those moods, and a note to my fans out there... don't take me literally... I think I'm crazy.
